```java
// 23-Feb-2015, tatu: Nasty, but has to do (for now)
if (_mapSerializer != null) {
    _mapSerializer.serializeFields((Map<?,?>) value, gen, provider);
    return;
}
// If we get here, the method just exits without doing anything
```

The problem is that when `_mapSerializer` is null, the method exits without serializing the map entries. We need to manually serialize the map entries when the serializer is null.

